sequenceDiagram
    participant D as Dashboard
    participant C as Controller
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant Disp as Dispatcher
    participant A as Agent

    Note over D,C: 1. Job Submission
    D->>C: DashboardCreateJobMessage<br/>(product, duration)
    C->>DB: INSERT JobRecord<br/>status = QUEUED
    Note over D: Dashboard snapshot #1<br/>job appears as QUEUED
    C-->>D: DashboardSnapshotMessage<br/>(jobs: [..., {status: QUEUED}])

    Note over C,Disp: 2. Dispatch
    C->>Disp: try_dispatch()
    Disp->>DB: SELECT queued jobs (FIFO)<br/>SELECT online agents with<br/>matching capabilities
    Disp->>DB: UPDATE job → ASSIGNED<br/>UPDATE agent → BUSY
    Disp->>A: JobAssignMessage<br/>(job_id, product, duration)
    Note over D: Dashboard snapshot #2<br/>job ASSIGNED, agent BUSY
    C-->>D: DashboardSnapshotMessage<br/>(job: ASSIGNED, agent: BUSY)

    Note over A: 3. Execution
    A->>A: Start job execution
    A->>C: JobStatusMessage<br/>(status: RUNNING)
    C->>DB: UPDATE job → RUNNING<br/>started_at = now()
    Note over D: Dashboard snapshot #3<br/>job is RUNNING
    C-->>D: DashboardSnapshotMessage<br/>(job: RUNNING)

    A->>A: await sleep(duration)

    A->>C: JobStatusMessage<br/>(status: PASSED, result: "...")
    C->>DB: UPDATE job → PASSED<br/>completed_at = now()<br/>agent → ONLINE
    Note over D: Dashboard snapshot #4<br/>job PASSED, agent back ONLINE
    C-->>D: DashboardSnapshotMessage<br/>(job: PASSED, agent: ONLINE)

    Note over C,Disp: 4. Next job cycle
    C->>Disp: try_dispatch()<br/>(check for more queued jobs)
